<div  class="contextual-help-item principal-help"  i18n:domain="novaideo">

	<p tal:condition="request.view_name == 'seemycontents'" i18n:translate="">
        You will find under "My contents" the ideas and proposals of which you were the author, and the proposals for which you were a participant in the working group. You will also find there all your archived ideas.
    </p>
    <p tal:condition="request.view_name == 'seemyparticipations'" i18n:translate="">
	    You will find under "My working groups" the proposals for which you participate in the working group.
    </p>
    <p tal:condition="request.view_name == 'seemyselections'" i18n:translate="">
        You will find under "My favourites" all the ideas, proposals and members that you have previously noted as your favourites.
    </p>
    <tal:block tal:condition="request.view_name == 'seemysupports'" >

      <div tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="request.support_ideas and request.support_proposals" >
        <p i18n:translate="">
            You will find under "My appraisals" the published ideas and the proposals submitted for appraisal to which you have allocated a support token or an opposition token.
        </p>
        <p i18n:translate="">
            You have a total of seven tokens that you are free to allocate to and to take away from any published idea or any proposal submitted to appraisal. Each token can be used to support an idea or a proposal, or to oppose it. To support or oppose an idea or proposal, you must first click on it.
        </p>
        <p i18n:translate="">
            In addition, you may also support or oppose proposals submitted for appraisal in which you participated in the working group. In this case, these special tokens are not counted against your initial reserve of seven appraisal tokens. Once allocated, these special tokens cannot be re-used for other proposals.
        </p>
     </div>
     <div tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="request.support_ideas and not request.support_proposals" >
        <p i18n:translate="">
            You will find under the tab "My appraisals" the published ideas that you have supported or that you have opposed.
        </p>
        <p i18n:translate="">
            You have a total of seven appraisal tokens that you are free to allocate to and to take away from any published idea or any proposal submitted to appraisal. Each token can be used to support an idea or a proposal, or to oppose it. To support or oppose an idea or proposal, you must first click on it.
        </p>
     </div>
     <div tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="not request.support_ideas and request.support_proposals" >
        <p i18n:translate="">
            You will find under the tab "My appraisals" the proposals submitted for appraisal that you have supported or that you have opposed.
        </p>
        <p i18n:translate="">
            You have a total of seven tokens that you are free to allocate to and to take away from any published idea or any proposal submitted to appraisal. Each token can be used to support an idea or a proposal, or to oppose it. To support or oppose an idea or proposal, you must first click on it.
        </p>
        <p i18n:translate="">
            In addition, you may also support or oppose proposals submitted for appraisal in which you participated in the working group. In this case, these special tokens are not counted against your initial reserve of seven appraisal tokens. Once allocated, these special tokens cannot be re-used for other proposals.
        </p>
     </div>
    </tal:block>

    <tal:block tal:condition="request.view_name == 'seealerts'" >
        <p i18n:translate="">The pictogram <span style="color: red" class="icon glyphicon glyphicon-bell"></span> indicates the latest warnings that you have received.</p>
        <p>
         <span i18n:translate="">You have received a warning:</span>
         <ul>
            <li i18n:translate=""> lorsqu'une idée ou une proposition vient d'être publiée et que l'un des mots clés correspond à vos centres d'intérêt,</li>
            <li i18n:translate=""> lorsqu'il se passe quelque chose sur vos idées ou les propositions auxquelles vous contribuez ou vous avez contribué,</li>
            <li i18n:translate=""> lorsqu'un membre vous communique une idée ou une proposition,</li>
            <li i18n:translate=""> lorsqu'il y a une réponse à l'un de vos commentaires,</li>
            <li i18n:translate=""> lorsqu'il se passe quelque chose sur une idée, une proposition, un membre que vous avez mis en favori.</li>
        </ul>
        </p>
    </tal:block>

</div>